# Git Repository Investigation Notes

## Git Overview
Analyzing a git project to understand how repositories store information and how hidden data (flags) can exist in commit history, branches, and files. Interpreting repository data using command line git tools or a web interface.

Git → Version Control System → Tracks code changes and revision history  

Common hosting services:
- Github
- Gitlab

A git repository contains:
- Files
- Commit history
- Branches
- Metadata about authors and changes

You can interact with repositories through:
- Command Line Interface (CLI)
- Web browser interface

---

## Cloning a Repository (CLI)

Command used to download a repository locally:
git clone [git repository url]


This command:
- Creates a new directory with the repository name
- Downloads all files and commit history
- Allows navigation and inspection locally

---

## Useful Git Commands
git log

Shows commit history on the current branch


git log [branch name]

Shows commit history for a specific branch


git show [commit hash]

Displays changes (diff) introduced in a commit


git branch

Lists available branches in the repository


git checkout [branch name]

Switches to another branch

Git output is often paginated:
- Up / Down arrows → scroll
- Space bar → next page
- `q` → quit pager

---

## Accessing a Git Repository Through the Web

Original repository format:


git@[hostname]:[username]/[repository name].git


Breakdown:

hostname → Server hosting the repository  
username → Owner of the repository  
repository name → Root directory of the project  

To convert to a browser-accessible URL:


https://[hostname]/[username]/[repository name]


Opening this URL allows browsing the repository through a graphical interface.

---

## Repository Exploration Strategy

Ways to locate hidden information in a repository:

- Check commit history
- Inspect commit diffs
- Look through branches
- Open repository files
- Review commit messages

Flags may appear in:
- README files
- Additional branches
- Hidden commits
- Commit messages
- Text files

